Jenkins Pipeline Mental Model

Note1:
pipeline
agent
parameters
environment
options
stages
stage
steps
post

Note2:
stage
  → when
  → steps
    → container
      → dir
        → withCredentials
          → script, only for Groovy logic
          → sh


input(...) {
    // Nothing is allowed here
}

timeout(...) {
    // Steps to run within the timeout
}

when - is used at stage level
parallel - is used at stage level
if-else - is used at steps level and inside a script block. It's complete groovy syntax
Jenkins Pipeline steps do not have names.


post {
    failure means the step/build failed
    unstable means the build completed, but there were issues
    success means everything passed
    always runs regardless of result
}

